<title type="html"><![CDATA[TMS9918 clone]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8608&amp;p=89853#p89853"><![CDATA[
Someone made a <a href="http://hardware.slashdot.org/story/12/02/11/2035226/tms9918a-retro-video-chip-reimplemented-in-fpga-with-vga-out" class="postlink">TMS9918 clone on an FPGA</a>. TMS9918 is the VDP in the ColecoVision, MSX, and TI-99/4A. The nearly pixel-perfect port of Donkey Kong to the ColecoVision <a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=5039" class="postlink">inspired</a> Nintendo to work on its own console. I wonder how hard it'd be to make an open source clone of the NES PPU and put it on opencores.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sat Feb 11, 2012 2:50 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
